layers.nm: How Do We Keep the Shore in Place?

Bare soil on a steep bank A measurable change of the shoreline over the short term Leaning or downed trees with exposed roots on the shoreline Excessive deposits of sand or other sediments on the streambed, or very wide, shallow areas in a stream.

Shoreline Erosion is a process that wears down or carries away rocks, soils, and/or sands along the coast. Shoreline erosion is a naturally occurring process but it can also be amplified by man-made disturbances and cause many problems.
